        <content><![CDATA[<p>In the tab "Element settings" you can configure element settings. These settings are shown when you click the <img style="width: 14px;" title="propertyBigIconActive" src="%(link0)" alt="" /> symbol at an element that is rendered with the formatter. The content editor can alter these settings to adjust the behavior of the formatter. A demo on how to use element settings is found <a href="%(link1)">here</a>, some more explanations are given <a href="%(link2)">here</a>. You can also link to a configuration file with already configured <a href="%(link3)">common element settings</a>, which are reused by many other formatters.</p>
<p>In OpenCms 11, the tab "<a href="%(link4)">Meta mappings</a>" was added, where you can set which values should be available to the page template as a meta mapping.</p>]]></content>
